SIMPLE: solicitor
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Solicitor
<hw>So*lic"it*or</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>solliciteur</ets>, L. <ets>sollicitator</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>One who solicits.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>An attorney or
advocate; one who represents another in court; -- formerly, in English
practice, the professional designation of a person admitted to practice
in a court of chancery or equity. See the Note under
<er>Attorney</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The law officer of a city,
town, department, or government; <as>as, the city <ex>solicitor</ex>;
the <ex>solicitor</ex> of the treasury.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Solicitor-general</ent>⟦br⟧
